Document: XRPositionalTracker
Path: godot/classes/class_xrpositionaltracker.rst
Summary: Provides tracking data for XR devices like controllers and head-mounted displays.

XRPositionalTracker

Inherits: Node3D < Node < Object

A node that provides tracking data for XR devices. This node is typically used to represent the position and orientation of XR devices such as controllers or head-mounted displays (HMDs). It automatically updates its transform based on the tracking data provided by the XR runtime.

Properties:
    tracker_name (String, read-only): The name of the tracker. This is usually provided by the XR runtime and can be used to identify specific devices.
    tracker_type (TrackerType, read-only): The type of the tracker. This indicates whether the tracker represents a HMD, a controller, or another type of XR device.
    has_position (bool, read-only): Whether the tracker provides position data. Some trackers might only provide orientation data.
    has_orientation (bool, read-only): Whether the tracker provides orientation data.

Methods:
    get_tracker_name() → String: Returns the name of the tracker.
    get_tracker_type() → TrackerType: Returns the type of the tracker.
    get_position() → Vector3: Returns the current position of the tracker in the XR system's coordinate space. Returns Vector3.ZERO if has_position is false.
    get_orientation() → Basis: Returns the current orientation of the tracker as a Basis in the XR system's coordinate space. Returns Basis.IDENTITY if has_orientation is false.
    get_velocity() → Vector3: Returns the current linear velocity of the tracker in the XR system's coordinate space. Returns Vector3.ZERO if the XR runtime does not provide velocity data.
    get_angular_velocity() → Vector3: Returns the current angular velocity of the tracker in the XR system's coordinate space. Returns Vector3.ZERO if the XR runtime does not provide angular velocity data.

Enums:
    TrackerType:
        TRACKER_HMD (0): Represents a head-mounted display.
        TRACKER_CONTROLLER (1): Represents a controller.
        TRACKER_GENERIC (2): Represents a generic tracking device.
        TRACKER_UNKNOWN (3): Represents an unknown tracker type.
