Document: XRPositionalTracker
Path: godot/classes/class_xrpositionaltracker.rst
Summary: Describes the XRPositionalTracker class, which represents tracked XR devices like controllers and anchor points.

An instance of this object represents a device that is tracked, such as a controller or anchor point. HMDs aren't represented here as they are handled internally.

As controllers are turned on and the XRInterface detects them, instances of this object are automatically added to this list of active tracking objects accessible through the XRServer.

The XRNode3D and XRAnchor3D both consume objects of this type and should be used in your project. The positional trackers are just under-the-hood objects that make this all work. These are mostly exposed so that GDExtension-based interfaces can interact with them.
---CHUNK---
Document: XRPositionalTracker
Path: godot/classes/class_xrpositionaltracker.rst
Summary: This document describes the XRPositionalTracker class in Godot Engine.

XRPositionalTracker

Inherits: Node3D < Node < Object

A node that tracks the position and orientation of an XR device.

This node is used to track the position and orientation of XR devices such as controllers, head-mounted displays, or other tracked objects. It provides methods to get the device's transform, velocity, and other tracking-related information.

Methods
-------

.. rst-class:: classref-method

.. rst-class:: instance-method

.. _class_XRPositionalTracker_method_get_tracker_transform:

get_tracker_transform() → Transform3D

Returns the transform of the tracker. This transform is relative to the XR rig's origin.

.. rst-class:: classref-method

.. rst-class:: instance-method

.. _class_XRPositionalTracker_method_get_tracker_velocity:

get_tracker_velocity() → Vector3

Returns the linear velocity of the tracker. This velocity is relative to the XR rig's origin.

.. rst-class:: classref-method

.. rst-class:: instance-method

.. _class_XRPositionalTracker_method_is_tracker_available:

is_tracker_available() → bool

Returns true if the tracker is available and providing data.

Properties
----------

.. rst-class:: classref-property

.. rst-class:: instance-property

.. _class_XRPositionalTracker_property_tracker_name:

tracker_name

:   string

    The name of the tracker. This can be used to identify specific trackers, such as "left_hand" or "right_hand".

.. rst-class:: classref-property

.. rst-class:: instance-property

.. _class_XRPositionalTracker_property_tracker_type:

tracker_type

:   int

    The type of the tracker. This can be used to determine the kind of device the tracker represents, such as a controller or a headset. Possible values are defined in the `TrackerType` enum.

Enum TrackerType
    TRACKER_CONTROLLER = 0
    TRACKER_HEAD = 1
    TRACKER_GENERIC = 2
    TRACKER_HAND = 3

.. rst-class:: classref-property

.. rst-class:: instance-property

.. _class_XRPositionalTracker_property_visibility_action:

visibility_action

:   string

    The action name that controls the visibility of this tracker. This is useful for hiding or showing trackers based on user input or game logic.
